on 6/20/02 8:31 PM, Jared Sims at utvolk(-at-)hotmail.com wrote:

> I've got a 79' 2.0L Westy which needs a new clutch. I'm in the process of
> dropping the engine now. My question is, are there some screws  underneath
> the bus that hold the front engine tin (that goes from one side to the
> other) to the motor? I've got all the screws I can see off the top and
> bottom, and the damn thing stil won't come off. It feels like it's still
> connected somewhere on the driver's side, but I can't tell for sure. If I
> can get that off, I should be in the clear (right?). Anything else a first
> timer like myself should pay close attention too?

This is all that come off:

http://homepage.mac.com/ratwell/.Pictures/78%20Camper/14%2DEngineTin.JPG

The long rectangular piece is the heat shield and screws secure it to the
engine tin. There is a "hidden" screw in the center of the middle just
behind the rear valence that you may have forgotten.

The big piece at the "back" where the firewall is comes off with the engine,
like so:

http://homepage.mac.com/ratwell/.Pictures/78%20Camper/26%2DEngineOutBack.JPG

